  "notes": [
    "This comparative genomics study reveals significant species-specific differences in hepatocellular carcinoma mutation patterns between chimpanzees and humans",
    "TSC2 mutations are dramatically more frequent in chimpanzee HCC (80%) compared to human HCC (7%)",
    "Chimpanzee HCC shows higher overall mutation burden but lower proportion of non-synonymous mutations compared to humans",
    "The study suggests different evolutionary pressures and oncogenic pathways between species"
  ]
